==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Bicarbonate
<hw>Bi*car"bon*ate</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Pref.
<ets>bi-</ets> + <ets>carbonate</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>A
carbonate in which but half the hydrogen of the acid is replaced by a
positive element or radical, thus making the proportion of the acid to
the positive or basic portion twice what it is in the normal carbonates;
an acid carbonate; -- sometimes called
<altname>supercarbonate</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

